She turned to an empty page and wrote the date on it. Below the date, she wrote: "5/11/648-12/13/648".
"Is she reflecting on the past?" Avery asked, looking at the old notebook. Carly nodded. "Do you think they'll let you out for Christmas? It's just a few days until Christmas."
Carly tapped on the lantern twice, indicating "no". As expected, Ice King never allowed Carly to leave the castle, as she was considered a "flaw" in his eyes. Carly was born mute and was the only girl in the family; all the other children were boys.
Avery was similarly treated, albeit in a unique way. When Avery came out as non-binary, the world seemed to change too. As punishment for being different, Avery was mostly assigned solitary work.
Avery was also forced to be the princess's servant. But Avery didn't mind because Avery had a friend.
"Your birthday is coming up, right?" Avery asked, remembering that it would be the princess's birthday in just a few days. Carly nodded, a hint of sadness flashing in her light blue eyes.
"Do you want to celebrate?" TA asked, recalling how Carly had answered this question last time.
No. Carly tapped on the table. Avery knew this was a difficult topic for Carly. On this very day, she was imprisoned in this room while her mother was executed. Avery was a baby at the time, but TA remembered the anger of the servants and citizens. TA had heard that Queen Elvina was a good queen and could even predict future events.
"So... what do you want to do?" TA asked. Carly looked up at TA, excitement in her eyes. She handed Avery a piece of paper. But when he bent down to look...
6 inches X 6 inches canvas
White, varying shades of blue paint
six brushes of different sizes
a easel
"Do you want me to get these things for you?" Avery turned to the silent princess, who was tapping away, her pigtails swinging back and forth. "Right?" She couldn't help but giggle when she saw how enthusiastic this usually quiet princess was about something. This was the first time she wanted something outside her room, and it wasn't related to books.
"Okay! See you later?" Avery said as she stood up and walked through the messy papers and notebooks.
Carly nodded and continued to curl up in the thick blanket, reviewing her memories.
TA walked out of the room, feeling relieved that the princess was finally willing to try new things and had made some requests outside her capabilities (such as paint).
TA once again passed through the hall, trying not to pay attention to the maids' whispered conversations.
"I heard she's possessed by Queen Elwin, so she always goes to that room."
"I heard she eats children in that room."
"She looks like a man. Is that normal?"
TA couldn't bear to listen to these words any longer and had to cover their ears. TA went to the room of the royal painter, which was in the east wing, second door on the left.
Avery approached the door, which was as ornate as Carly's. The door was adorned with a white dragon, one of the six primal dragons, said to have created the Frostlands. The painter's passion for history made it unsurprising that the white dragon was depicted on the door.
TA opened the door, expecting everything to be as usual. For example, there were supposed to be paints everywhere, pencils and papers scattered around, and easels covering every inch of the walls. However, the scene inside was quite different. The room was clean, with a red velvet backdrop and a stool. Aquilo, the crown prince, was sitting on the stool, painting a portrait.
"Oh, good morning, Avery! Want to see the portrait of your future king?" Aquilo asked, winking at Avery.
"Sorry, Prince," she replied, beginning to look around for what Princess Carley wanted.<s/> "I just came to collect some art supplies."
"Little one, must you go so soon?" Aquelo asked, "But I still want to see you!"
"I don't want to." Avery found the art supplies on the list and put them in a box. "And, I'm not a girl."
The prince was dismissive. "Oh, dearie, you know this is just a phase! It'll be fine when you grow up!" he mumbled.
"I have to go." She said, feeling increasingly uncomfortable as the prince continued talking. She recalled all the negative comments about her gender identity. I really want to get away from him.
"Are you leaving so soon?" The prince suddenly appeared at the door, ignoring the shouts of the royal painter.
"This is not the behavior a future king should have!" TA said sternly.
"No one will know. People won't believe him if the painter values his life, and he wouldn't say anything rash." The prince glanced at the painter before leaning close to Avery. "Do you think a date sounds good?" TA shivered in fear. Of course, TA had heard many threats before, but none came from the prince, let alone this future king.
"Do you know what the word 'no' means?" TA roared, pushing the crown prince away.
"No," Aquero replied with a smile. This crown prince, who could have anything he wanted, naturally didn't know what the word 'no' meant.
Avery rolled his eyes. "Why do you want to date me out of all the people? How many suitors do you have? One hundred?"
He laughed and interrupted, "To be precise, it's more than five hundred." He shook his hair, swaying in the cold wind.
"See! Why me? I am the bane of the palace." She crossed her arms.
"You're the most beautiful girl I've ever seen," Aquiro said, placing a finger under Avery's chin to force him to look up at him.
